<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
First, I'd like to start by saying Greetings to my fellow Sorcerer brothers and sisters.  This is my 1st post here, I guess because I'm normally just a quiet lurker on the boards.  Well I think its time I joined in.<P>Second, I would like to thank i3ullseye for his help with our class.  I dont always agree with you, but I know your heart is in the right place and mean well for the class.  I do not fault you for the problems we are having or lack of attention we are getting.  All I can ask of you is that you keep the faith and keep trying for the sake of us all.<P>Third, I want to appologize for the following Rant.  I know of nowhere else better to let off steam on our situation than the best Sorcerer boards I can find on the web.  I respect all your opinions and welcome your comments.<P>I utterly hate being Mythic's token NERF class.  Doesn't seem to matter who was target of their nerf, somehow Sorcerer's always seem to be on the receiving end of the bat.  Don't get me wrong, I love my Sorcerer and there is nothing I'd rather play more, probably why its so hard to swallow the BS that is force fed to us (and we are paying for it...I have receipts).<P>The nerf to our Mesmerize line in RvR hit us hard.  I dont see how they think its ok for an Armored Tank to be able to charge at you, Instantly cast a stun on you, then proceed to beat the living snot out of you, but a Cloth wearing Twig of a Caster must stop FULLY, begin casting (can be interrupted), cant fight back worth a damn, and when the spell actually sticks he cannot have his way with you for the duration of the spell like you can with a stun.  How are these 2 even close.  Mez should never have been touched with the timer for us.<P>Debuffs are another sore area.  I originally planned to take Mind to 44.  No longer.  Debuffs now do next to nothing, not worth casting when a nuke is a better option, because its faster casting, less mana, does DAMAGE to kill target quicker, and will provide "REALM POINTS".  Debuffs before the nerf I agree were a bit too strong.  Though I dont think they were far off base.  If we debuffed a target would should be able to drop their stats to 1 (ONE) at the minimum if spell was strong enough, otherwise why else cast them.  I agree maybe a percentage based replacement would work best...say maybe 7 spells in each line, 1st spell does 15%, 2nd does 25%, 3rd does 35%, 4th does 50%, 6th does 65% and 7th does 80%.  In the case of Str and Dex where they are repeated in another line, just have it debuff current debuffed stat by listed percentage, never to drop a target below 10% of their "BASE" stat.  This would make them worth casting again and it wont really overbalance anything.  If I can get one maybe 2 shotted by Archers even Runemasters now, why cant we debuff the living crap out of you making you a saucy target for either our tanks or our nukes???<P>Charm....oh boy, give a tank class, with instacasts, the best pets in the game now???  Are Sorcerers THAT OVERPOWERED that it'd of killed Verant (oops Mythic) to have given us the ability to charm higher level mobs back??  Not to to mention that they can HEAL THEM TOO...while we go through pets like a hobo on a ham sandwich, then have to go find another disposable hero to fight for us.  I say give us a way to heal our pets during NON-COMBAT downtime, I dont care how....life transfer, whatever.....or allow us to charm ALL MOBS short of quest mobs, epic mobs, vendors, etc.<P>Confusion....my god I loved this spell up til that last nerf.  Now I am only lvl 25, but that lvl 20 Mystify Mind spell with its measly 15% to attack other mobs really made a difference....even with the warping (god awful annoying).  The damn spell worked as ADVERTISED!!!  What next nerf the Healer's ability to heal....well because its works too damn well?  It allowed us to kill a mob that you didn't want killed....god I really think Verant is hidden partners with Mythic.<P>Other Items I'd like to see changed...Amnesia, with its sickning power cost would actually be used if it made you loose your target on top of interrupting you...as someone said before, how long can you keep this up with this kind of power cost?<P>Confuse in RvR, shorten the times all of the levels to 20 or 30 seconds and have each tic of time randomly choose a different target (Including Allies).  Now you shouldnt be able to hurt then by any means, but it would be annoying as hell...maybe unbalancing...shrug....but you could put one of your "great" (sarcasim) timers on it.  Say one could not be confused again for another 30 seconds to a minute???<P>Charm in RvR, I know this is just asking for it, but wouldn't it be great to be able to charm someone for 30 seconds to a minute and make him fight his own allies...after which if he survived, he(sorry ladies no disrespect) could not be charmed again until he zones or dies....makes good use of a spell that doesnt last too long....<P>Snare/Root spells in general I've noticed that if I sticks as mob hits me, when I try to back away they keep coming.  I realize it only slows them to like 1%....but damn dont we walk backwards faster than that?<P>Grouping...we are a great great great class for grouping, but at lower levels we just are not wanted....at all...unless you have alot of time to spend finding a group, make one, or have a built in group (personal friends).  I think someone said it once before that its mainly cause at these levels there isnt much diversity....other classes can do our job albiet not as well, but well enough.  Again, mainly due to encounters dont force them into situations where LARGE numbers of mobs attack (until later levels).  I dont think we need other spells to make us more group friendly, cause thats just not the Sorcerer thing....though some good spells in the Matter line could be a way to work towards the goal of making us more wanted during the lower levels....dunno really.<P>I think I got it all...lol.  Though I'm probably leaving out stuff.  Again I appologize for the long post.  I hope this comes across the way I want it too....I'm not the best at putting thoughts to paper.  Anyway, please post comments, flames, ideas, whatever really.  I really enjoy this forum here...finally decided to leave EQ for good and come make DAOC my home for now, and would like to see maybe a petition of somekind started with all our thoughts and best ideas for fixes, additions, etc. started and maybe e-signed with all us bumping it then send the link to the Pendragon forum (dunno if they'll follow it but hey).  Maybe start with this thread to hash out our ideas, then i3ullseye can start another with all the best ideas and post the link...<P>Well now I think I'm rambling on too long.<BR>Peace,<P>--------------------<P>Shyann Silvermane<BR>Dark Sorcerer of Albion
</FONT>
